com.emc.vipr.client.system

Class LogMessageProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.emc.vipr.client.util.AbstractItemProcessor<LogMessage>
      • com.emc.vipr.client.system.LogMessageProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ItemProcessor<LogMessage>

    public abstract class LogMessageProcessor
extends AbstractItemProcessor<LogMessage>
    Item processor for LogMessages. This allows for one-by-one handling of LogMessages returned from the Logs API without storing all in memory.

    For example: 

     ViPRSystemClient client = ...
 // dump logs to standard out without holding any in memory
 client.logs().search().items(new LogMessageProcessor() {
     public void processItem(LogMessage item) throws Exception {
         System.out.println(item.getSeverity() + " " + item.getTime() + " " + item.getMessage());
     }
 });
